9.title: About Easter on April Fools, but Not Really

episode of.title: This Is What I Think (TV Series 2018– )

9.plot: Jude and Donny discuss what they think about filming on Kids These Days, driving PSA's, Six Flags, Easter cantatas, the Apple company, Jaguar autonomous driving, Toys R Us going out of business, Build a Bear, Carl's Jr., the Spielburger, Black Coast, the MLS All-Star game, and next week's special guest Marc with a "C" Collins.

10.title: About Marc the Collins

episode of.title: This Is What I Think (TV Series 2018– )

10.plot: Jude and Donny discuss what they think about, special guest and co-host, Marc Collins' reoccurring role on Kevin Probably Saves the World, auditions, Kelley Young at AWP, Ferrari of Atlanta, Hit the Marc dance move, spring break destinations, a galaxy without dark matter, prom-proposal vs. proposal, Watson twins, pollen, Shaq, Braves mascot, The Weekend and Selena breakup, Fig the hairstylist's dog, Stranger Things fan surprise, and being an actor.

13.title: About ATL Film Festival and Perfect Atlanta

episode of.title: This Is What I Think (TV Series 2018– )

13.plot: Jude and Donny discuss what they think about attending the Atlanta Film Festival, Re:imagine/ATL, Suburbia by Sierra Isley and Brooks Sullivan, auditioning for Rings season two, Jordan-Paige Sudduth, Kendall Hanzlik, Christian Adam on NBC's Good Girls, DC vs. Marvel, Guy Fieri, Fortnite and Overwatch, EG3, Manchester City and Manchester United, Logic, Grammys, and Kendrick Lamar.

14.title: About Movie Screenings and Plastic Pollution

episode of.title: This Is What I Think (TV Series 2018– )

14.plot: Jude and Donny discuss what they think about eating at Come N Get It, voiceover workshops, Kids These Days, Cameron Vandiver, LED movie screen, the Dolby theater in LA, Avenger Infinity Wars, plastic eating enzymes, Julio Jones, prehistoric whale fossils, Destined 2 B Yours special mention at the global shorts festival, Jordan-Paige Sudduth, Lenny Kravitz, NFL draft, Shaquem Griffin, Guardians of the Galaxy, Tesla, and The Greatest Showman.

15.title: About May the Fourth and Cinco de Mayo

episode of.title: This Is What I Think (TV Series 2018– )

15.plot: Jude and Donny discuss what they think about the Bradford twin's project, the Caffeine and Octane car show, Foo Fighters, Walk a Moment in Someone Else's Shoes screening with Jordan-Paige Sudduth, Rob Pralgo, Cinco de Mayo, May the fourth, Mark Hamill, Marvel studios, Avengers, Infinity War, the McLaren P1, the draft recap, and the yodeling kid's new hit single Famous.
